phases.content:
Update the desktop frontend so it can render parallel phase indicators.

### TypeScript type changes

**apps/desktop/src/components/work/WorkCard.tsx** (canonical IssueContext for the desktop app):

1. Add an interface near `PhaseInfo`:

```ts
export interface ParallelExecutionInfo {
  phases: number[];
  completedInGroup: number[];
  totalInGroup: number;
  startedAt: string;
}
```

2. Add to `IssueContext`:

```ts
parallelExecution?: ParallelExecutionInfo;
```

3. In the existing `WorkCard` body, wherever the `phase.current / phase.total` text is rendered, add an inline parallel badge when `work.parallelExecution && work.parallelExecution.phases.length > 1`. Render it next to the existing 'Phase X of Y' text:

```tsx
{work.parallelExecution && work.parallelExecution.phases.length > 1 && (
  <span className="parallel-badge" title={`Phases ${work.parallelExecution.phases.join(', ')} running in parallel`}>
    parallel: {work.parallelExecution.phases.length}
  </span>
)}
```

**apps/desktop/src/components/sidebar/WorkProgressCard.tsx**: this component already imports `WorkContext` from `WorkCard`, so the type flows automatically. Render the same `parallel-badge` next to `Phase {currentPhase}/{totalPhases}` inside `<span className="work-progress-text">`. Read via `isIssue ? work.parallelExecution : undefined`.

**apps/desktop/src/components/detail/IssueDetail.tsx**: the local `WorkContext` interface (lines ~14-24) is hand-rolled. Add to it:

```ts
parallelExecution?: {
  phases: number[];
  completedInGroup?: number[];
  totalInGroup?: number;
  startedAt?: string;
};
```

No UI rendering required in IssueDetail beyond keeping the type valid.

**apps/desktop/src/stores/tikiStateStore.ts**: imports WorkContext from `../components/work` — no change needed.

**apps/desktop/src/App.tsx**: uses WorkContext from work components — no change to TikiState needed.

**apps/desktop/src/components/kanban/KanbanBoard.tsx**: uses an inline `{ phase?: ... }` cast — no change needed since it doesn't read parallelExecution.

**apps/desktop/src/components/sidebar/IssuesSection.tsx**: same — inline cast, no change needed.

### CSS

Append a `.parallel-badge` rule to **apps/desktop/src/components/sidebar/WorkProgressCard.css** (and a matching one near the existing `.work-card` styles in App.css if `WorkCard` uses App.css). Reuse existing color vars:

```css
.parallel-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-left: 8px;
  padding: 1px 6px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.18);
  color: #60a5fa;
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  vertical-align: middle;
}
```

### Update shared types (defensive)

For symmetry with Rust and to avoid drift, also extend **packages/shared/src/types/state.ts**:

```ts
/** Parallel execution tracking (optional, present only during parallel phase groups) */
export interface ParallelExecution {
  phases: number[];
  completedInGroup: number[];
  totalInGroup: number;
  startedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

Add to `IssueWork` and `ReleaseWork`:

```ts
/** Parallel execution group tracking (set only when phases > 1 are running concurrently) */
parallelExecution?: ParallelExecution;
```

Also add the field to **packages/shared/schemas/state.schema.json** under `issueWork.properties` and `releaseWork.properties`:

```json
"parallelExecution": {
  "type": "object",
  "description": "Parallel execution tracking (set only during multi-phase parallel groups)",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "phases": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 1 } },
    "completedInGroup": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 1 } },
    "totalInGroup": { "type": "integer", "minimum": 1 },
    "startedAt": { "$ref": "#/$defs/timestamp" }
  },
  "required": ["phases", "totalInGroup", "startedAt"]
}
```
